    "Existing black-box RAG methods [36,44,53,54] typically fine-tune the retriever only based on LLMs' preferences (e.g., whether LLMs can give correct answer with the retrieved documents) and concatenate all the retrieved documents as the input, which suffers both effectiveness and efficiency issues.",
    "Only considering LLMs' preferences in retrieval causes ignorance of factual information, which can degenerate the effectiveness of RAG for it may mislead the retriever.",
